[{"id":"c53ab05c7d362f72bdcaed99d316ab8f","from":"Lesley Groff","from_email":"lesley@nysgllc.com","to":"J. Epstein","to_list":[{"name":"J. Epstein","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"FW: Manhattan User's Guide: Eyes","date":"2008-04-15T12:47:04.000Z","formatted_date":"Apr 15, 2008","formatted_time":"12:47 PM","body":" \n\n \n\nFrom: Dr. Henry Jarecki [mailto:hj@falconfone.com] \nSent: Monday, April 14, 2008 8:29 PM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nSubject: FW: Manhattan User's Guide: Eyes\n\n \n\n \n\nThis is at the frick and I thought you might not yet have heard of it.  Closes 4/27.\n\n________________________________\n\nFrom: MUG Newsletter [mailto:newsletter@manhattanusersguide.com] \nSent: Monday, April 14, 2008 9:53 AM\nTo: hj@falconfone.com\nSubject: Manhattan User's Guide: Eyes\n\n \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/index.php> \nManhattan\rUsers Guide <http://http:/www.manhattanusersguide.com/> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/send_to_friend.php?id=1291> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/contact.php> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/change_address.php> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <mailto:ads@manhattanusersguide.com> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/article.php?id=1291> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/email/info.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\nEyes\n\nApril 14, 2008\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\nToday, the eyes have it.\n\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/aux/041408a.jpg> \nWe're not sure that the French eye drops Gouttes Bleues <http://www.newlondonpharmacy.com/innoxa/apothecary-products.htm>  are actually good for your eyes. However, they do give them a noticeably bright sparkle that we've never gotten from anything else. \u2028\n\n\n\n\nOver 52,000 people have had their sight restored through corneal transplants made possible by donations to the Eye-Bank for Sight Restoration <http://www.eyedonation.org/> . Sign up to be a donor here <http://www.eyedonation.org/sign.html> .\n\n\n\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/aux/041408b.jpg> Finding a perfect mascara can be an elusive pursuit, but many people think Diorshow <http://www.sephora.com/browse/product.jhtml?id=P40404>  is pretty close. Available in black as well as azure blue and chestnut. \n\n\n\n\n\nFor 70 years, H. L. Purdy Opticians has been the gold standard in eyewear stores (they have two shops on Madison, one on Lexington). They can also do a lot of fancy handiwork when it comes to customizing <http://hlpurdy.com> : they'll put your prescription into everything from telescopes to opera glasses to diving masks. They can even hand-paint a frame to match an outfit. \n\n\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/aux/041408c.jpg> \nThe grays of winter are finally giving way to eye-opening colors, as these magnolia trees next to Cleopatra's Needle in Central Park show.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/aux/041408d.jpg> \nLast chance to feast your eyes on Parmigianino's Antea, the exquisite painting that makes a solo exhibition at the Frick <http://www.frick.org/exhibitions/Antea/index.htm> . It closes on April 27th.\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/email/bar_sponsor.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/sponsor_links.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\nDiscover the Alexander Technique. Re-discover your natural ease. Are you living with undue tension? Discover this practical method for better posture, less pain, and mind-body integration. Uncover you body's innate ease. Certified instructor Amira Glaser introduces this holistic approach to easier moving, breathing and being. For more information: visit www.amiraglaser.com <http://www.amiraglaser.com/> .\n\n\u2022\n\n\nA MET PREMIERE: Philip Glass's landmark opera Satyagraha is a moving, musical meditation on Mahatma Gandhi's formative experiences in South Africa, which shaped his visionary philosophy of Satyagraha (Sanskrit for \"truth-force\"). Experience this sensational new production, created by Phelim McDermott and designer Julian Crouch (Shockheaded Peter), fresh from its hit run in London. Improvisational puppetry and evocative projections come together in what The Times (London) called a \"masterwork of theatrical intensity.\" 6 performances left! April 14, 19 mat, 22, 25, 28, May 1. Visit metopera.org <http://www.metoperafamily.org/metopera/season/production.aspx?id=9251>  or call (212) 362-6000 for ticket availability.\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/joe_info.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n\nwilliamsburg <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/large.php?s=20080414>  \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/radar_info.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/aux/clicks.jpg> \nClicks\n\n\u2022 Another Sign of Progress for Brooklyn Greenway <http://www.streetsblog.org/2008/04/11/another-sign-of-progress-for-brooklyn-greenway/#more-3705> \n(Streetsblog)\n\u2022 The Emir of NYU <http://nymag.com/news/features/46000/> \n(NY Mag)\n\u2022 Lego City Of The Future, By Norman Mailer & Friends <http://greg.org/archive/2008/04/08/lego_city_of_the_future_by_norman_mailer_friends.html> \n(greg.org)\n\u2022 Otterness Does DUMBO <http://gothamist.com/2008/04/13/otterness_does.php> \n(Gothamist)\n\u2022 Practical city living, #9: Useless emergency signs <http://maudnewton.com/blog/?p=8464> \n(Maud Newton)\n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/email/bar_bottom.gif> \n\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\n\t\n\t\t\n <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/img/blank.gif> \n\nSubscribe <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/subscribe.php> \n\n  |  \n\nUnsubscribe <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/unsubscribe.php> \n\n  |  \n\nArchive <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/archives.php> \n\n  |  \n\nPrivacy Policy <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/privacy.php> \n\n  |  \n\nAbout Us <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/about.php> \n\n  |  \n\nContact Us <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/contact.php> \n\n  |  \n\nChange Address <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/change_address.php> \n\n  |  \n\nRSS <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/rss/mug.rss> \n\n\u00a9 2000\u20132008 Manhattan User's Guide. All rights reserved. Reproductions of any portion of this website\nonly at the express permission of Manhattan User's Guide, Inc. Terms & Conditions <http://www.manhattanusersguide.com/terms.php> \n\n \n\n","body_html":"<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" xmlns:m=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40\">\n\n<head>\n<meta http-equiv=Content-Type content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\n<meta name=Generator content=\"Microsoft Word 12 (filtered medium)\">\n<!--[if !mso]>\n<style>\nv\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\no\\:* {beh